              "ImageUrl": "step_1_6.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_7.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "For sambhar masala preparation, dry roast coriander powder for a minute. Swich off the stove and add chilly and methi powder and mix it well. Once it cools down, grind it into a fine paste.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_3.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Soak tamarind in warm water for 30 mins, squeeze out the tamarind juice then add it to the pressure cooked dal along with sambhar masala. Allow it to come to boil.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Meanwhile grind the grated coconut to a smooth paste. Once the dal starts boiling add the coconut paste and curry leaves. Reduce the flame and let it simmer for 7-8 mins.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "For tempering, in a pan heat oil then add mustard seeds and allow it to splutter. Then add hing and switch off the stove. Add this tempering to dal.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
